The paper discusses the topic of agent-based negotiation teams, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also mentions the use of computation and parallelization capabilities, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The joint work of agents with different expertise and skills is also mentioned, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG). The representation of different stakeholders or preferences in the same party is related to social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the challenges related to agent-based negotiation teams may also involve human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
